# Phase: Speaker Diarization with sherpa-onnx

**Goal**: Integrate sherpa-onnx for local speaker diarization to map transcript segments to individual speakers with persistent identification across meetings.

## Overview

**Solution**: Use [sherpa-onnx](https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx) — a production-ready library with Rust bindings that provides:
- **Offline speaker diarization** (no cloud API required)
- **Speaker segmentation** via pyannote models
- **Speaker embedding extraction** via 3D-Speaker or NeMo models
- **Speaker identification** with persistent speaker database
- **Multi-language support** (language-agnostic, works with Indonesian/English/Mandarin)
- **5+ speaker support** (tested with multiple speakers)
- **Rust API** with examples at `rust-api-examples/`

## Architecture

```
Audio File
    ↓
[Transcription] ← Whisper API (existing)
    ↓
[Speaker Diarization] ← sherpa-onnx (NEW)
    ├─ Speaker Segmentation (pyannote model)
    └─ Speaker Embedding Extraction (3D-Speaker/NeMo)
    ↓
[Segment-Speaker Mapping] (NEW)
    ↓
Enhanced Transcript with speaker labels
```

## Dependencies to Add

### Cargo.toml (crates/core)

```toml
[dependencies]
# Existing dependencies...

# Speaker diarization
sherpa-onnx = "1.10"  # Check latest version
```

### Pre-trained Models (to download)

**Speaker Segmentation Model** (choose one):
- `sherpa-onnx-pyannote-segmentation-3-0` (recommended)
  - URL: https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx/releases/tag/speaker-segmentation-models
  - Size: ~16 MB (model.onnx) or ~5 MB (model.int8.onnx, quantized)

**Speaker Embedding Model** (choose one):
- `3D-Speaker` (recommended for quality)
  - URL: https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx/releases/tag/speaker-recongition-models
  - sherpa-onnx-3dspeaker-speech-campplus-sv-zh-cn-16k-common.onnx
- `NeMo` (alternative, smaller)
  - sherpa-onnx-nemo-titanet-en-large.onnx

Models will be stored at: `~/.meeting-agent/models/`

